Title: Object: Fertilization of Egypt
Description: Illustration from Erasmus Darwin's "The Botanic Garden" (London, 1791); draped nude figure of the dog-headed god Anubis, seen from behind; standing with his legs astride the Nile; pyramids and clouds in the background; behind Anubis a gowned, bearded, winged figure hovering over the water, arms outstretched. 1791 Engraving and etching
Dimensions: Height: 215 millimetres (trimmed within platemark (publication line trimmed))
Bibliographic references: Essick 1991 / William Blake's Commercial Book Illustrations (XXI(1))
